<p>This is a list of <b>notable Amish and their descendants</b>, including both those who lived or are living culturally as <a href="/wiki/Amish" title="Amish">Amish</a> or <a href="/wiki/Amish_Mennonite" title="Amish Mennonite">Amish Mennonite</a> as well as those who recognize themselves culturally as Amish or Amish Mennonite descendants but may or may not practice <a href="/wiki/Anabaptist" class="mw-redirect" title="Anabaptist">Anabaptist</a> beliefs. This list does not include those of <a href="/wiki/Mennonite" class="mw-redirect" title="Mennonite">Mennonite</a> religion only, who are not culturally connected to Switzerland and South Germany and the persecution documented in the <i><a href="/wiki/Martyrs_Mirror" title="Martyrs Mirror">Martyrs Mirror</a></i>.
</p><p>To be included in this list, the person must either have a Wikipedia article showing they are Amish or Amish Mennonite or are of Amish or Amish Mennonite descent or must have references showing their claim and are notable. 
</p>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg/220px-Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="145" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg/330px-Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg/440px-Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2262" data-file-height="1486" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Amish_life_in_Lancaster_14503v.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Amish in Lancaster, Pennsylvania</div></div></div>
